product_name: Anastasia Beverly HillsLip Velvet Full-Pigment Lip Mousse
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeIntroducing new! Anastasia Beverly Hills Lip Velvet, a velvet-smooth lip mousse with weightless, full pigment, true-matte color, cushioned, comfortable wear and a smoothing lip finish that allows you to line and apply with a multifunctional, teardrop-shaped cushioned wand.
details: DetailsBenefitsSoft-focus, velvety-smooth finish will diffuse the appearance of lip textureWeightless, true-matte color will offer effortless, always polished lip looksCushioned, comfortable wear will move with you without feeling heavy and dryTeardrop-shaped cushioned wand allows you to both line and apply for one-swipe, on-the-go colorEasy to apply for all skill levels‚Äîespecially beginnersColor appears seamlessly natural, smoothing and moisturizingPlush and elastic feeling with a soft focus effectFuller-bodied, rich mousse textureItem 2618187How To UseUsing the point of the wand, trace cupids bow to center lip shape and line outer edges. Gently swipe flat paddle edge of wand across lips in one smooth gesture for full-pigment, true-matte soft focus color.IngredientsDimethicone, Dimethicone/Vinyl Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Isododecane, Silk Powder, Tribehenin, Polyglyceryl-2 Triisostearate, Vinyl Dimethicone/Methicone Silsesquioxane Crosspolymer, Vp/Hexadecene Copolymer, Diisostearyl Malate, Lauryl Peg-9 Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone, Sorbitan Sesquiisisterate, Triethoxycaprylylsilane, Polyglyceryl-2 Diisostearate, Fragrance/Parfum, Benzyl Benzoate, Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499)Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Using the point of the wand, trace cupids bow to center lip shape and line outer edges. Gently swipe flat paddle edge of wand across lips in one smooth gesture for full-pigment, true-matte soft focus color.

reviews.headline: Not Worth it even with the discounted price
reviews.comments: I love matte lip wears and this one was a huge disappointment. The color was nice, however it dried up my lips which I dislike for matte colors. I had higher expectations especially being a name brand like Anastasia. The color did not last even and hours. DO NOT BELIEVE THE POSITIVE COMMENTS. Unless the other women didnt mind the lipwear not being long lasting. Honestly the Maybelline matte liquid lipsticks last longer and wear better than this one.

reviews.headline: I would buy this again
reviews.comments: I bought a very neutral color. It's almost too light for me. I still wear it. You can change your lip liner to change the color. The applicator is good. Glides on smooth.  Puts just enough on your lips for a perfect coverage. It doesn't last all day, but it doesn't claim to. So it's okay for me.

reviews.headline: Great lipstick except for color
reviews.comments: I have anout 5 of these lip velvets. I love them for the consistency, smoothness and staying power, I haven't found anything that compares. However, the colors are all very orange and theres little variation between some colors. Some tones, such as softy, kiss and pink sand, are not as pink as they appear and have an orange cast, so I always need to adjust the color with another lipstick.

reviews.headline: My goto!
reviews.comments: This is the only lipstick that I will wear. I remember in 2016 those matte lipsticks were so dry and so patchy this is the exception this is an absolutely beautiful formula. It lasts all day even on the inner parts of my lip when I'm drinking and eating at work, it doesn't budge. Sometimes I'll top it with a gloss and I'll use a darker lip liner to add some depth. I own two colors: a rosey mauve and the cool brown color. Sometimes I blend them together to kind of give a little bit more definition. This is absolutely wearable and it doesn't break my skin out because I have ultra sensitive skin so that is another plus please never discontinue this product. It is beautiful.

faceoff_positive.comments: Anastasia Beverly Hills' new Lip Velvet Liquid Lipstick is perfection in a matte, nude colored lip formula! Upon first opening this liquid lipstick, I wasn't sure about the shade itself. I was a little intimidated by the shade Parchment looking at it through the tube. Looks can be deceiving, because once I applied the peachy brown shade, I was pleasantly surprised by how lovely it was! With that being said, I was in awe over the formula itself! It's amazingly lightweight to the point of feeling like a feather brushing against the lips. Given that it's a matte formula, I was even more impressed by how buttery-smooth it applied & how creamy it was when rubbing my lips together to disperse evenly. I literally felt like I was applying a moisturizing treatment to my lips. That immediate satisfaction continued even after I had it on for a while. Matte lip formulas have come a long way. It's not as difficult to find a product in a matte finish that feels hydrating going on, but after some time has passed, I can usually still differentiate between a matte or, for example, a satin. With the new Lip Velvet Liquid Lipsticks, I can't tell that it's a matte formula unless I look in the mirror. This liquid lipstick continues to lend that creamy moisture to the lips while feeling light as a feather! The texture feels super luxurious while providing a beautiful matte finish to the lips that blurs my fine lines & other little imperfections. This particular formula not only enhances my lips, but it also gives a fuller appearance. The lasting power was impressive as well, to say the least. Obviously, most of us would expect a matte formula to withstand several hours, but not one that feels like a lightweight, whipped formula that still manages to also feel rich & velvety smooth! Clearly I can't stop raving over the new Lip Velvet Liquid Lipstick in the shade Parchment thanks to its optimal quality and performance. This formula translates to...a matte, liquid lipstick at its best!
faceoff_positive.headline: Perfection in a Nude Colored Lip!

faceoff_negative.comments:
First, I'd like to thank Buzz Agent and Anastasia for the opportunity to be among the first beauty enthusiasts to take Lip Velvet, their latest lipstick line, for a test drive via two free samples of the 6 available colors. In return, I'm sharing an absolutely honest review based solely on my personal opinion of this lipstick.
I received Lip Velvet in Crush and Parchment. Both are dominantly neutral, however "Parchment" appears slightly orangish and is a tad darker while "Crush" is lighter and leans just a little towards pink. I'm describing the shades because I found the color represented on the package is different than the actual product, especially Parchment, which appears much darker and a different hue. The applicator wand is oval but flat with a slight angle, which makes it  easy to apply both the top and bottom evenly. I also like the twist and lock design, you know the tube is locked up tight, so you won't find the lid rolling around in your bag. The texture is luxurious, it glides across your lips just  like the name says‚Ä¶velvet. It feels soft and clean, not even in the realm of sticky. It's a semi gloss/semi matte finish, very contradictory but true. It does go on much lighter than color depicted on the box, more like a tint or stain.
I spent a full day wearing each shade and surprisingly, there were a couple major differences. First, I used Crush and not what a mess! This lipstick was seriously everywhere! There were little "lumps" all around my lip line, these quickly spread to my hands, shirt, forehead and my lips looked like I smeared chocolate ice cream all over my mouth! I almost didn't want to try the other shade after the previous days experience, but I wasn't going anywhere so I gave it a go. This one didn't clump or smear at all, it looked quite nice and fit my lip shape and defined the cupids bow, but definitely not a good color match for my skin tone. Also, this is NOT a long wearing lip color. I had to reapply it 30 minutes after I put it on
faceoff_negative.headline: Super messy, was on more than my lips!
